Check out the latest blog from Dr. Devin Vicknair regarding how behavioral health connects to community wellness.

http://ow.ly/TbvF50z0g7v
shared_text:
United Way of Hall County
March 17 at 4:40 PM ·

During this time of "social isolation", it can be more difficult to find ways to make connections, but as Dr. Devin Vicknair points out in the latest Reach Out blog, "There is power when people come together to support the health of their community...As people organize fund raisers, support organizations...volunteer and simply listen to their neighbors, community health increases. Remember, you can make a difference in the lives of others."

Read more from Dr. Vicknair at https://www.unitedwayhallcounty.org/behavioral-health-and-community-wellness/

post_text: Are you interested in becoming a HAM Radio Operator? You CAN become a licensed Ham Radio Operator and it is easier than you may have imagined! The GMS Amateur Radio Club is hosting a one-day Ham Radio Licensing event "Ham Cram" on Saturday, March 14th from 8 am - 3 pm at GMS. Participants will review for the FCC exam and then take the exam onsite. The event is free with a $15 FCC exam fee. Lunch will be provided. For details, contact Craig Bailey at n4gcs@gcssk12.net. Register at http://ow.ly/Zlc050yGZRD.
text: Are you interested in becoming a HAM Radio Operator? You CAN become a licensed Ham Radio Operator and it is easier than you may have imagined! The GMS Amateur Radio Club is hosting a one-day Ham Radio Licensing event "Ham Cram" on Saturday, March 14th from 8 am - 3 pm at GMS. Participants will review for the FCC exam and then take the exam onsite. The event is free with a $15 FCC exam fee. Lunch will be provided. For details, contact Craig Bailey at n4gcs@gcssk12.net. Register at http://ow.ly/Zlc050yGZRD.
